  "body": "Random musing I was having:\r\nIs it possible to write an HTTP GET Method implementation in EVM where the resulting data is some JSON object queried by a base URL (with  standardized query terms) with some quantified and guaranteed key path (e.g. if the requested key path doesn't exist in the queried data, `throw`)\r\n\r\nThis is probably more of a general EVM question, I was thinking about it from a language point of view, like it be very useful to create a set of simple and common oracle interactions as a Viper language feature. @DavidKnott what do you think?",
