    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I really don't see how the EVM should or could be able to access off-chain resources. Contract code is run on all validators. That would mean hundreds or thousands of requests to the same URL. Also, this would make contract executions non-replicable.\r\n\r\nSay, a state change is conditional of an off-chain URL. A few blocks ago it succeeded. Now it would fail. How do you validate that block? It's literally impossible, you need to take the miner's (validator's) word for it that the URL returned a valid result at the time. Maybe they are lying, maybe not.\r\n\r\nI'm sure there are some things that are best implemented in layer 2, and oracles, in my opinion, are one of them.",
